    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix SRS normalized channel IQ matrix unpacking error handling\n\n### Summary\nThe `unpack_nr_srs_normalized_channel_iq_matrix` function in the nFAPI library was incorrectly returning success (0) instead of failure (-1) when encountering buffer read errors during channel matrix data unpacking. This caused downstream processing to proceed with potentially corrupted or uninitialized data.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/src/nfapi_p7.c`: Corrected return value from 0 to -1 on line 6170 when `pull8` operation fails during channel matrix unpacking.\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain network conditions with malformed SRS indication TLVs, the function would return 0 indicating success even though the channel matrix data was not properly unpacked. This led to downstream gNB processing using invalid channel state information, causing beamforming calculations to produce incorrect results and potentially leading to UE connection drops.\n\nThe issue can be observed when running OAI gNB with SRS-based beamforming enabled and receiving corrupted SRS reports from UEs or simulated RF sources.\n"
}